g.text: User authenticates with an external service
(e.g. facebook, google, etc) via OAuth
User grants profile access rights (basic) to
the application
User gets an unique id based on the
authentication domain and an authentication
token. Application associates user id with
access token and sets an expiration date for
the access token
User is eligible for accessing the API (has
permission to access API endpoints). Application
checks each subsequent request to see if user
provided the correct api key (used at
authentication) and the api key is not expired
User confirmes his identity by sending an
authenticated request to associate a provided
email address with his authenticated user id
User receives a confirmation code on the
provided email address and submits it in the
web application
Confirmation code is valid
User has confirmed its faculty identity
Application can access the external account details
